Steps taken to create profits and losses tableau visualation project

1. Connect Data

Load Sample - Superstore dataset (Orders sheet key for Sales, Profit, Category, Sub-Category, Region, State, Order Date).

2. Key Calculations

Profit Ratio: SUM([Profit]) / SUM([Sales])
Optional: Profit Flag for coloring (IF [Profit] >= 0 THEN "Profit" ELSE "Loss" END)

3. Build Core Sheets

Sub-Category Profit Bar: Sub-Category on Rows, Profit on Columns; sort descending; red-green diverging color; add labels.
Category Profit: Similar bar or stacked, detailed by Sub-Category.
Profit Map: State on Detail â†’ auto-map; Profit on Color (red-green).
Profit Trend: Order Date (Month/Year) on Columns, Profit on Rows (line); optional dual-axis Sales.
KPIs: Text sheets for Total Profit, Sales, Profit Ratio (large formatted numbers).

4. Dashboard Assembly

Add title "Profits and Losses".
Layout: KPIs top; map left, main bar right; trend bottom.
Add filters: Year, Region, Category (apply globally).
Actions: Filter on selection, highlight on hover.

5. Polish & Publish

Consistent red (loss) / green (profit) palette.
Custom tooltips, currency formatting.
Publish to Tableau Public.
